The app is delivered via a .zip file. This file can then be imported at [https://make.powerapps.com/](https://make.powerapps.com/) (Solutions -&gt; Import Solution). On the right side of the screen, the import dialog opens. Use the Browse button to select the file.

In the next step, under Advanced Settings, you can choose whether the package should be installed as an upgrade, phase for upgrade, or as an update.

- Upgrade – an update for the currently installed version.

- Phase for Upgrade – a patch version, for example, to implement bug fixes. The .zip file contains only the files to be updated.

- Update – overwrites the previous installation.

The installation process may take a few minutes. In the list of solutions, the entry "Doxee Workspace" with the new creation date and version number will be displayed, or MS Dynamics will also display a pop-up message at the top of the browser once the app has been successfully installed.
